WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.336
Well, good evening family. Thank you for joining me again tonight.

00:00:04.337 --> 00:00:13.697
We're going to pray and go over some of the things that have happened in the news in the last 48 hours or so.

00:00:13.698 --> 00:00:17.957
It's been a good weekend. I pray you've had a wonderful weekend. The weather's been nice.

00:00:17.958 --> 00:00:23.316
We've gotten some rain, and so, giving Jesus all the glory for the rain.

00:00:23.317 --> 00:00:28.719
Isn't it wonderful? Things start to get really green whenever the rain comes.

00:00:28.720 --> 00:00:37.079
I love it. The flowers, everything—the animals love it. Everything gets happy for the rain.

00:00:37.080 --> 00:00:42.733
Father, we thank you for all the rain that we've had. Thank you for all the rain we have in the forecast this week.

00:00:42.734 --> 00:00:50.816
We're so grateful for all the rain that you've given us. And I thank you that it's going to rain from sea to shining sea.

00:00:50.817 --> 00:00:58.179
We call in the rain. We thank you, Lord, that the drought is broken in the name of Jesus.

00:00:58.180 --> 00:01:05.594
We call it in again this week already; we call it in from the north, the south, east, and the west.

00:01:05.595 --> 00:01:13.719
We thank you, Lord, that the rain is coming on the jet stream as the low-pressure system is bringing it forth.

00:01:13.720 --> 00:01:19.174
But not only that, Father, we thank you, Lord, that it stalls out and just keeps dumping on our area.

00:01:19.175 --> 00:01:27.719
I thank you, Lord, that we would have enough to fill up our lakes, our ponds, our streams, our rivers, and Father, our reservoirs.

00:01:27.720 --> 00:01:35.119
Father, we thank you, Lord, that we have at least five inches this week in Jesus'name to get out of the deficit.

00:01:35.120 --> 00:01:41.799
Everybody say amen on that. You agree for your area because you don't just stop whenever you just get a little bit.

00:01:41.800 --> 00:01:47.758
That's the beginning; whenever you make it a greasy spot, you keep praying and calling the rain in in the spring.

00:01:47.759 --> 00:01:56.919
Well, Brandon, isn't it supposed to rain in the spring? Yes, but we had a major drought and we have to catch up.

00:01:56.920 --> 00:02:12.983
And so, for those of you who are having a lot of rain, don't take it for granted because fires are terrible when everything's burning up and you go, 'Man, we've got to have rain quick.'All right.

00:02:12.984 --> 00:02:20.555
So, okay, we have a lot of news here, Braden. This is where I'm at with...

00:02:20.556 --> 00:02:37.519
that's the chat. I don't want to see it. It moves in my eye whenever I see all those people talking.

00:02:37.520 --> 00:02:48.529
I want to say this. Oh, so we see the Sooners come out. Do you remember when I told you Japan will be the Sooner concerning crypto?

00:02:48.530 --> 00:02:55.719
Japan, South Korea—I said they will be the ones that implement things before America.

00:02:55.720 --> 00:03:09.083
And you'll start to see Japan implement the crypto laws and really try to go after it like America will in the days ahead. But I called them the Sooners.

00:03:09.084 --> 00:03:19.132
And I said, 'I saw the Boomer Schooner wagon.'If you're familiar with OU college football, they have a Schooner wagon.

00:03:19.133 --> 00:03:25.518
Well, every time they make a touchdown, they run out that wagon and celebrate the touchdown.

00:03:25.519 --> 00:03:40.039
And I said, 'This is what you're about to see.'I said, 'I saw Sooners coming across Japan and South Korea in the days ahead.'So Braden said, 'Daddy, the word is coming to pass.'Do you see it?

00:03:40.040 --> 00:03:47.556
Yeah. Is something wrong? Right. Okay. See this article right here?

00:03:47.558 --> 00:03:53.079
I don't know—some of this stuff, you have to be careful. There are a lot of scammers, but this is a good one.

00:03:53.080 --> 00:04:05.596
Braden says, 'Okay, Japan officially approves bill to recognize cryptocurrency as a financial asset.'The Sooners.

00:04:05.597 --> 00:04:16.854
Ain't that neat? I thought that was so cool. I said, 'Look, Lord, it's happening.'Just like you said, Japan is announcing their recognition of cryptocurrency.

00:04:16.855 --> 00:04:23.479
The Sooners are at work. They're sending out the wagon. Here we go.

00:04:23.480 --> 00:04:33.180
Then we have the little gray-headed guy saying about America and Coinbase coming out and saying it's time to get it done.

00:04:33.181 --> 00:04:42.119
Do you have that? No. Oh, you don't? Okay. Do you have anything about...

00:04:42.120 --> 00:04:49.014
well, I thought that's what we were talking about. I'm sorry. I've been exercising. I've been out trying to do walks.

00:04:49.015 --> 00:04:56.713
So, I haven't had time to talk to Braden before it got dark because I'm trying to get this weight down as quickly as possible.

00:04:56.714 --> 00:05:05.712
I've gotten 25 going on 30 lbs off and I'm giving God all the glory for it. You know, the older I get, it seems...

00:05:05.713 --> 00:05:14.713
when I was in my 20s, it fell off a lot faster, but now I have to work harder, it seems. But that's all right. We're going to get it off.

00:05:14.714 --> 00:05:25.159
And I told Diana, I said, 'You know, just watching your calories and exercising.'I've been walking, taking walks, and it's fun, I guess.

00:05:25.160 --> 00:05:35.999
Woohoo! But Paisley likes it. All right, here is the guy that's over Coinbase.

00:05:36.000 --> 00:05:48.116
We agree. So Scott—this SEC Scott—he said they want to get the Clarity Act done.

00:05:48.117 --> 00:05:52.514
Basically, he's making an announcement saying, 'We've got to get this Clarity Act done.

00:05:52.515 --> 00:06:03.559
You all have to stop delaying.'And then the guy that's over Coinbase is saying, 'We agree.

00:06:03.560 --> 00:06:18.319
We agree it's time to pass the Clarity Act.'So the Sooner is before this. The Treasury Secretary...

00:06:18.320 --> 00:06:28.439
Congress has spent the better part of half a decade trying to pass a framework to onshore the future of finance.

00:06:28.440 --> 00:06:35.028
And so I said, 'What are we going to see in the days ahead? A Clarity Act.'That's what we're going to pray about.

00:06:35.029 --> 00:06:43.453
We keep praying about it and I said I saw the boys—Donald Trump's sons—with the coins and they were dancing and they were going into the new building.

00:06:43.454 --> 00:06:51.519
They had a big building and I said I saw the building start growing and it doubled the building that they had.

00:06:51.520 --> 00:06:58.517
So when you're looking into a vision, I don't try to add to or take away from anything, but what is it talking about?

00:06:58.518 --> 00:07:16.199
Was that building their real estate empire? I tried to figure out what the Lord's trying to say without being flaky about it.

00:07:16.200 --> 00:07:33.992
But when I saw that building standing there and it was all the Trump letters, and then I saw this new tower start to grow and it had digital all in it, and it started to make the real estate building where they are at now look really small compared to what they're about to do.

00:07:33.993 --> 00:07:45.400
And Barron came on the scene. Now I don't know how far Barron has left school, if he's going to college or whatever, but I'm sure he is. And if he's getting a Master's or whatever, who knows?

00:07:45.401 --> 00:07:56.159
But I know that I saw Barron come into the building and all of a sudden Barron made the whole building start having digital writing on it.

00:07:56.160 --> 00:08:08.119
And I saw Eric leading them in. But Barron was the mastermind. His mind was the one that was running this thing more.

00:08:08.120 --> 00:08:13.559
Eric went and then all of a sudden the building started to come alive.

00:08:13.560 --> 00:08:29.150
If everybody remembers that vision that I had about a week ago, I just get excited about it when they start talking this stuff because I'm believing God for a financial turnaround for the body of Christ, for the wealth of the sinners laid up for the righteous.

00:08:29.151 --> 00:08:35.446
And I believe in the name of Jesus, we're going to see it sooner than later. I keep standing on it. I'm not letting it go.

00:08:35.447 --> 00:08:55.255
As we hear everybody talk about the markets crashing and things looking bad—'Oh no, the sky is falling, Chicken Little'—I believe that as for me and my house, we're going to be blessed and we're going to keep standing, regardless if the Great Depression is going all around us and we have a major 1929-style crash.

00:08:55.256 --> 00:09:07.231
I remember a preacher talking and he said, 'During the Great Depression, my mom and daddy never went without anything.'He said, 'They always tithed.

00:09:07.232 --> 00:09:14.589
They always gave. They always sowed to the church. And God always took care of them during the Great Depression.

00:09:14.590 --> 00:09:19.994
They never lacked anything. They always made their house payment. They always had food on the table for us kids.

00:09:19.995 --> 00:09:26.377
They always had all this.'And he was talking about how God always provided even in the Great Depression.

00:09:26.378 --> 00:09:33.942
Now, if you're talking about my granny who was 106 when she went home to be with the Lord, they struggled.

00:09:33.943 --> 00:09:42.319
They didn't believe in tithing. They didn't believe in giving. I don't even think they were really good Baptists.

00:09:42.320 --> 00:09:47.839
They were Baptist, but I don't even think they were really good Baptists. They were just kind of lukewarm Baptists even at that.

00:09:47.840 --> 00:10:21.810
She said, "Brendon, we had to eat black crow, you know, the big black crows flying around in the sky."She goes, "Daddy would go out there and shoot those black crows and we would eat crow pie, blackbird pie, black crow pie, and we would try to make it out of whatever we had to."Then she goes, "And if those became scarce because people were killing all the crows off, we started eating possum."She said, "We'd go down in the creek beds and look for possums and we'd start eating possum."I said, "Granny, what did possum taste like?"She said, "It tastes like gristly, really fatty.

00:10:21.811 --> 00:10:54.039
It was real oily because the possum was real greasy."She said, "We used to try to fry it because we were starving."She goes, "And I'll never forget getting those flour sacks from the feed store and Mama couldn't give us good clothes and we were growing as kids, so she would always make us feed store sack clothes."Even up until Granny went home to be with the Lord at 106, she would always go out in the ditch and find stuff to eat.

00:10:54.040 --> 00:11:00.029
She'd go out there and all kinds of poke greens and lamb's quarter, whatever she could find.

00:11:00.030 --> 00:11:10.519
She'd go out there and start digging in the yard and pull it up by the roots and she would cook it and eat it, and it stunk so bad. But she was healthy. She lived to be 106 years old.

00:11:10.520 --> 00:11:16.785
The only reason she went home was she fell and hurt her hip and they were going to put her in the nursing home and she willed herself to death.

00:11:16.786 --> 00:11:24.003
She said, "I'm not going to the nursing home."She gave up the ghost right there on the bed because she was determined not to go to the nursing home.

00:11:24.004 --> 00:11:29.252
She did not want to go or she'd probably still be here. She is a fighter.

00:11:29.253 --> 00:11:33.626
She wanted to live. But she didn't want to go to the nursing home and she was alive.

00:11:33.627 --> 00:11:41.399
She wanted to take care of herself. Even until then, to make a long story short, she took sponge baths.

00:11:41.400 --> 00:11:47.361
Didn't have to; had money, but she wouldn't even take a bath in the shower.

00:11:47.362 --> 00:11:56.275
She would fill a pan up full of water and dip the sponge and take a sponge bath and wash her hair because she was so scared of not having, and she saved foil.

00:11:56.276 --> 00:12:02.198
She saved everything. But my point is that generation knew how to live off the land.

00:12:02.199 --> 00:12:09.552
They had some grit. Granny and them had some grit. She made the best buttermilk biscuits I ever had in my life.

00:12:09.553 --> 00:12:24.894
But I'm going to tell you that 10-year window for the Great Depression affected her for the rest of her life for decades to come.

00:12:24.895 --> 00:12:32.734
That financial lack that hit America shook her for decades and decades.

00:12:32.735 --> 00:12:44.377
And that was when she was just a young girl. That tells you how we're so blessed; our generation is so blessed.

00:12:44.378 --> 00:12:50.399
We've never tasted that kind of stuff. That was only 100 years ago.

00:12:50.400 --> 00:13:00.599
1929 will be 100 years in the next couple of years. I'm not trying to say all that to freak you out.

00:13:00.600 --> 00:13:04.559
I've seen it again and again. And that's what I'm trying to tell you.

00:13:04.560 --> 00:13:14.632
If we are the body of Christ, we must learn how to give. We must learn how to trust God for a great shaking to awaken.

00:13:14.633 --> 00:13:21.519
Do I believe we're going to see 1929? I pray with all my heart we don't.

00:13:21.520 --> 00:13:36.439
But history seems to repeat itself. People are asleep. What is the mechanism to the revival?

00:13:36.440 --> 00:13:45.316
What brings what we're looking for? What is the first domino?

00:13:45.317 --> 00:13:54.959
It seems that America is stiff-necked and God's going to get their attention somehow.

00:13:54.960 --> 00:14:08.439
I just think it's interesting to me. As I pray into all this stuff and as we see this, what did I tell you we would see?

00:14:08.440 --> 00:14:11.205
What the Holy Spirit warned us about President Trump, the war, and all the things.

00:14:11.206 --> 00:14:24.114
I said when the tariffs don't go into effect and we don't pray the Supreme Court justice to coincide with him, we're in the valley of decision.

00:14:24.115 --> 00:14:31.439
This was back in January. I said this will be a major turning point of his presidency.

00:14:31.440 --> 00:14:41.662
And I said the next phase will be war, war, war. I said Trump will be known as a wartime president.

00:14:41.663 --> 00:14:51.894
When he first started, I told you this over a year ago. He came out saying, "I'm full of peace.

00:14:51.895 --> 00:15:04.787
I want peace."But God will use him to shake the nations. He will crack his whip and he will shake the nations in making America great again.

00:15:04.788 --> 00:15:10.679
There will be a business side of him that we've never seen before.

00:15:10.680 --> 00:15:16.279
All gloves are off. Why? Because he's not going to be president again.

00:15:16.280 --> 00:15:19.986
We know we're out of time. He knows where the American economy is.

00:15:19.987 --> 00:15:26.879
But I said, "Watch what happens when he attacks Iran and attacks this area over there."It's going to happen.

00:15:26.880 --> 00:15:35.088
Remember, I said, "He'll go after Venezuela and he'll get Venezuela and then he's going to go after Iran."And guess what?

00:15:35.089 --> 00:15:42.159
It happened exactly the way the Lord said. You can go look through all the videos of every time the Lord warned us about it.

00:15:42.160 --> 00:15:55.119
And I said, "Then he will say, drill, baby, drill."And he did. We will take Iran back to the Stone Age and they will.

00:15:55.120 --> 00:16:14.040
When this takes place, I said people will start to buy oil from America and it will make America's economy booming again and it will look like everybody and their brother is coming to America to buy oil.

00:16:14.041 --> 00:16:26.263
Does anybody remember this stuff that I'm telling you? I said it will stimulate and there'll be oil all in the Gulf of America. There'll be oil coming out of Houston.

